curam.util.client.model

Interface Link

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public interface Link
extends java.io.Serializable
    A representation of a hyperlink. The link target is a path that resolves to the URI of the link and the named parameters are set to paths that resolve to the parameter values. The parameters are not automatically added to the target URI when the target path is resolved.

    • Method Detail

      • getLinkTarget

        Path getLinkTarget()
        Gets the path that resolves to the target URI of the link. This may be null.
        Returns:
        The path for the target URI.

      • getParameter

        Path getParameter(java.lang.String name)
        Gets the path that resolves to the value of the named parameter.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the parameter.
        Returns:
        The parameter value path, or null if there is no parameter with that name.

      • getParameterNames

        java.util.Collection<java.lang.String> getParameterNames()
        Gets a collection of the names of all of the parameters. These names can be passed to Link.getParameter(String) to get the value path. The collection is not modifiable. The iteration order of the names will be the same as the order in which they were set when the link was built.
        Returns:
        The collection of parameter names. It may be empty, but will never be null.
